      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(browser): bring tab to foreground before screenshot capture",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**What problem does this PR solve?**\n`browser screenshot` (and the screenshot-backed snapshot path) hang until the CDP socket times out (~20s) whenever the target tab is **backgrounded**.\n\n**Why does this matter now?**\nOn a multi-tab or node-hosted browser session, any capture of a non-foreground tab blocks for the full timeout, making screenshots effectively unusable without manual tab juggling.\n\n**What is the intended outcome?**\nCaptures return promptly regardless of which tab is foregrounded.\n\n**What is intentionally out of scope?**\nThe pure-a11y snapshot path (`Accessibility.getFullAXTree`) — it needs no rendered frame and already works on backgrounded tabs, so it is left untouched.\n\n**What does success look like?**\nA capture of a backgrounded tab returns in ~100ms instead of timing out.\n\n**What should reviewers focus on?**\nThat issuing `Page.bringToFront` before capture is acceptable behavior (it activates the target tab). It is a no-op for a single-tab session and for an already-foregrounded tab, and its failure is swallowed so capture paths that already work cannot regress.\n\n### Root cause\n`Page.captureScreenshot {fromSurface:true}` waits for a compositor frame to commit. Under `--headless=new`, a **backgrounded tab never commits a new frame**, so the call blocks until timeout. `Accessibility.getFullAXTree` is unaffected (no rendered frame needed) — which is why text/a11y reads succeed while pixel capture hangs. The capture path issued no `Page.bringToFront`/`Target.activateTarget` before capturing.\n\n### The fix\nIn `extensions/browser/src/browser/cdp.ts` `captureScreenshot()`, issue `await send(\"Page.bringToFront\").catch(() => {})` immediately after `Page.enable` and before capture. Activating the tab forces a compositor frame to commit.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #\n\nRelated # — none upstream; tracked downstream.\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner? No — external contribution.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `Page.captureScreenshot` hangs on backgrounded tabs under headless Chrome.\n- **Real environment tested:** OpenClaw browser node pod, Chromium `Chrome/148.0.7778.215` headless (`--headless=new --no-sandbox --disable-gpu --disable-dev-shm-usage`), ARM64, driven via CDP on the live debugger port.\n- **Exact steps run:** Over the browser's CDP endpoint, created two tabs (data-URL pages), activated the second so the first is backgrounded, attached to the backgrounded tab, then timed `Page.captureScreenshot` **before** vs **after** `Page.bringToFront` on the same session. Repeated 3x.\n- **Evidence after fix (the mechanism this patch applies):**\n\n  | run | backgrounded, no bringToFront | after `Page.bringToFront` |\n  |-----|-------------------------------|---------------------------|\n  | 1   | 3367 ms                       | **109 ms** |\n  | 2   | 3222 ms                       | **84 ms**  |\n  | 3   | 3260 ms                       | **117 ms** |\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Capture returns in ~100ms after `bringToFront`, vs multi-second (up to the full ~20s timeout on heavier real pages) without it.\n- **What was not tested:** I verified the exact CDP behavior the patch applies (bringToFront → capture) directly against a live headless browser; I did not additionally rebuild and run a full OpenClaw image end-to-end through the `browser` tool. The patch inserts precisely the call that was measured.\n- **Proof limitations:** A lightweight `data:` page degrades to ~3.3s rather than the full 20s a heavy page exhibits; the invariant (bringToFront → ~100ms) is identical in both, so before/after on the same tab is the load-bearing evidence.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- Targeted typecheck of the browser extension; the change is type-neutral (error-count delta vs the untouched base is 0 — the monorepo workspace deps are unbuilt in my checkout, so absolute-zero tsc isn't attainable there, but base == patched).\n- No new automated test added: the failure mode is a headless-Chrome compositor timing behavior that requires a real backgrounded tab to reproduce; covered by the real-behavior proof above.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- Did user-visible behavior change? **Yes** — capturing now foregrounds the target tab first.\n- Did config/env/migration behavior change? **No.**\n- Did security/auth/secrets/network/tool-execution behavior change? **No.**\n- Highest-risk area: `bringToFront` changes which tab is foreground in a multi-tab session.\n- Mitigation: no-op for single-tab/already-foregrounded sessions; `.catch(() => {})` tolerates failure so existing working captures cannot regress.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Next action: maintainer review.\n- Waiting on: maintainer.\n- Bot/reviewer comments addressed: none yet (initial submission).\n",
        "branch": "fix/browser-bringtofront-before-screenshot",
